Step 1. Calculate Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
• From the income statement:
  Gross Profit = 279378.77
  Total Revenue = 775598.77
• Gross Profit Margin = (279378.77 ÷ 775598.77) × 100% ≈ 36.00%

Step 2. Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities)
• From the cash flow statement and balance sheet:
  Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –967147.02
  Total Current Liabilities = 7605149.91
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = –967147.02 ÷ 7605149.91 ≈ –0.13

Thus, the solution is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "36.00%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-0.13"
  }
}
